 <purpose>
   This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to represent
   data identifying an item that is not fully represented in a population of instances of EXPRESS entity data types but is only referred to.
	 <example>An example of such a case is a digital file that contains documentation about a product and that is stored
	 on an external digital storage system.
	 </example>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
 <li>identification of an external source for a particular item;</li>
<li>identification on an item in the context of an external source where it can be found.</li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
 	<li>identification of the types of items that are considered as external items.</li>
 </outscope>

